Hide Global Search for Specific Lightning Apps

Give your users a more focused experience by hiding the global search for specific Lightning apps in your org. When they switch to another app, the search bar is visible again

This change applies to mobile connected apps.

How: This feature is enabled through a connected app setting, which you configure. The setting accepts one or more app developer names as its value. To see your lightning app developer names, open Lightning Experience App Manager.
title: Hiding Global Search in Salesforce Lightning Apps
